cars.name: Porsche 718 Cayman GTS 40
cars.description: The 2017 Porsche 718 lineup ranges from the 300 HP 2.0L turbocharged base model (7.4–8.2 L/100km) to the 493 HP 4.0L naturally aspirated GT4 RS (11.2–12.5 L/100km), with all models being strict two-seaters designed for thrilling performance and driver-focused dynamics..

cars.name: Land Cruiser V8 2016 XZ
cars.description: The 2016 Land Cruiser V8 ZX cossets you in hand-stitched leather, quad-zone climate control, and silent armor-plated refinement—all while its 4.5L twin-turbo diesel V8 (272 HP)  conquers continents at 10.5–13.8 L/100km. A fortress on wheels where brute capability meets CEO lounge.

cars.name: 2023 TOYOTA Helux GR
cars.description: The 2023 Hilux GR Sport slams a 2.8L turbo-diesel (201 HP/500 Nm) into a Baja-tough chassis, wrapped in GR-badged aggression—Bilstein dampers, Recaro bucket seats, and red-stitched defiance. It scoffs at 10.5 L/100km while out-dirting luxury SUVs at half the price.

cars.name: Lexus RX450 H Hybrid
cars.description: The Lexus RX 450h Hybrid blends a 3.5L V6 + electric motors (308 HP) with samurai-silent refinement, coddling passengers in semi-aniline leather while sipping just 6.7 L/100km (35 MPG). A tech-laden sanctuary with Mark Levinson audio, climate-controlled seats, and enough serenity to make a Zen monk jealous.

cars.name: Land Cruiser Prado TXZ (TZG)
cars.description: The Toyota Land Cruiser Prado TXZ (TZG) wraps full-leather captain’s chairs, wood-accented opulence, and tri-zone climate control around a 2.8L turbo-diesel (204 HP/500 Nm) or 4.0L V6 (282 HP) heart—conquering trails at 8.5–10.3 L/100km while coddling passengers like a mobile five-star lodge.

cars.name: 2024 Marcedez Benz E200
cars.description: The 2024 Mercedes-Benz E 200 blends mild-hybrid efficiency (1.5L turbo + EQ Boost / 204 HP) with bank-vault silence, swathing drivers in Nappa leather, ambient-lit opulence, and self-parking wizardry—all while sipping just 6.1 L/100km (46 MPG).

cars.name: BMW X5 (2024)
cars.description: The 2024 BMW X5 balances a 3.0L turbocharged inline-6 (375 HP)  in the X5 M60i) with Merino leather-wrapped indulgence, crystal gearshift theatrics, and self-leveling air suspension—all while delivering 9.1–12.3 L/100km depending on your right foot’s enthusiasm.

cars.name: Mazda CX5
cars.description: The 2024 Mazda CX-5 merges 2.5L SkyActiv-G (187–256 HP) with Kodo design elegance, swathing drivers in Nappa leather, Bose 10-speaker audio, and Japanese minimalist luxury—all while sipping a modest 7.8–9.0 L/100km (30–26 MPG).

cars.name: SUBARU Forester XT
cars.description: The Subaru Forester XT stuffs a 2.0L turbocharged Boxer-4 (250 HP) into its no-nonsense shell, pairing rally-bred Symmetrical AWD with 8.2 L/100km (29 MPG) efficiency—all while offering 5.8 seconds 0-100 km/h urgency and dog-friendly vinyl seats.

cars.name: BMW I8
cars.description: .The BMW i8 fused a 1.5L turbo 3-cylinder (228 HP) + electric motor (131 HP) into a carbon-fiber spaceship body, delivering 357 combined HP, 2.6L/100km (90 MPGe) efficiency, and 4.4-second 0-100 km/h thrills—all while looking like it time-traveled from 2030

cars.name: Audi A4
cars.description: The 2024 Audi A4 balances a 2.0L TFSI turbo (261 HP)  with Quattro AWD grip, swathing drivers in Valcona leather, virtual cockpit tech, and bank-vault refinement—all while delivering 6.3–4.5 L/100km (37–52 MPG).

cars.name: Honda sedan civic
cars.description: Honda sedans blend bulletproof 1.5L (130 HP) or turbo 1.5L (180 HP) engines with magic-seat practicality, delivering 5.2–6.7 L/100km (45–35 MPG) efficiency in packages ranging from the entry-friendly City to the tech-loaded Accord Hybrid.

cars.name: Toyota Axio XP150
cars.description: The Toyota Axio XP150 pairs a 1.5L 1NZ-FE (109 HP) or 1.3L (95 HP) engine with bulletproof simplicity, delivering 5.1–5.8 L/100km (55–49 MPG) efficiency with Apple CarPlay .

cars.name: Toyota Hiace
cars.description: The Toyota HiAce crams 3.0L turbodiesel (176 HP) or 2.7L  power into a bombproof steel shell, hauling 12 passengers or 3.5 tonnes of cargo at 7.5–9.2 L/100km (31–26 MPG) while outlasting civilizations.

cars.name: 2016 Toyota Voxy Hybrid
cars.description: The 2016 Toyota Voxy Hybrid combines a 2.4L 2AZ-FXE (150 HP) + electric motor hybrid system with sliding-door convenience, delivering 5.2 L/100km (45 MPG) efficiency while seating 8 in airport-shuttle comfort. A box on wheels that prioritizes kid-hauling logic over flash, with dual sunroofs and refrigerated storage for hot summers.

cars.name: 2019 Ford Ranger
cars.description: The 2019 Ford Ranger with a 2.3L EcoBoost turbo (270 HP / 310 lb-ft), a 7,500-lb towing capacity, and Terrain Management 4WD, packaged in a chassis that chews through job sites at 10.2 L/100km (23 MPG) while coddling drivers with SYNC 3 tech and 10-speed auto smoothness.

cars.name: Toyota Fielder
cars.description: The Toyota Fielder packs 1.5L (109 HP) or 1.8L hybrid (122 HP) power into a station wagon silhouette, delivering 4.5–5.8 L/100km (52–41 MPG) efficiency while swallowing bikes, IKEA hauls, or surfboards with magic-seat flexibility.

cars.name: 2016 Toyota Harrier (XU60)
cars.description: The 2016 Toyota Harrier (XU60) wraps a 2.0L turbo (231 HP) or 2.5L hybrid (197 HP) in a Lexus RX-inspired silhouette, gliding through cities at 5.8–7.2 L/100km (41–33 MPG).

cars.name: 2016 Toyota Probox
cars.description: The 2016 Toyota Probox stuffs a 1.3L (87 HP) or 1.5L (109 HP) engine into a plastic-lined toolbox on wheels, delivering 5.5–6.2 L/100km (43–38 MPG) efficiency while hauling 600kg of cargo, tools, or contraband produce across potholes that would kill lesser vans.

cars.name: LEXUS LX-570
cars.description: The 2016 Lexus LX 570 pampers with semi-aniline leather thrones, hand-sanded wood trim, and a Mark Levinson 19-speaker symphony, all while its 5.7L naturally aspirated V8 (383 HP/403 lb-ft) devours dunes at 16.8 L/100km (14 MPG). Seven seats, hydraulic suspension, and a silent, climate-controlled vault on wheels—this is royalty with a tow hitch.

cars.name: Porsche Panamera
cars.description: The Porsche Panamera fuses 3.0L V6 (330 HP) to 4.0L twin-turbo V8 (630 HP) power with hand-stitched Nappa leather, adaptive air suspension, and PDK lightning shifts, rocketing to 100 km/h in 3.1–5.5 seconds while cradling four adults in 18-way massaging seats. A 5m-long grand tourer that corners like a 911 and sips fuel like a CEO.
